Frequently Asked Questions
How much does it   cost? Our special rate of $39.95 (offer expires soon) gets you full lifetime access to   the Members' Area of our site, where you can access government auctions and bid   on all types of vehicles: cars, trucks, motorcycles, boats, and more.
What is in the Members'   Area? Click   here for a list of the products and services available in our Members'   Area.
Is the $39.95 a one-time   fee? Yes. You pay $39.95 one time, and you have full lifetime access to   our Members' Area. No monthly rebilling charges ever.
Do you have only Sheriff   Auctions, or are other auctions included too? In our Members' Area you   will get full access to all of the Sheriff Auctions, but as an added bonus at no   extra charge we also give you access to all kinds of Government Auctions and Private Sector Auctions so you   will get the biggest listings of auctions of  cars, trucks, motorcycles,   and boats available.
After I sign up, when can I   begin using your system? Upon our receipt of your payment, you will   have instant access. There is nothing to download, and you don't have to wait   for anything to arrive in the mail. All the resources you need to begin   participating in auctions of seized and forfeited vehicles and property are   located in our Members' Area.
Will I have to pay any   additional fees to bid in the auctions? The $39.95 Membership fee to   the Members' Area of our site is all you ever have to pay, and you will have   full access to all of the Sheriff Auctions and Government Auctions without   paying any additional fees.
Do I need a dealer's license? You will not need a dealer's license for many of the auctions in our Members' Area, because many of them are open to the general public. However, in the interest of making our Members' Area as complete as possible, we also include auctions where you would need a dealer's license in order to bid. In order to get a dealer's license, you would need to contact the DMV in your state and inquire about the procedure to obtain a dealer's license, if you want to bid in those particular auctions. 
Is there a   guarantee? Yes, within 30 days of your membership purchase, if you are   not satisfied we will refund your membership fee in full. After 30 days all   sales are final.
Can I bid on Sheriff   Auctions and Government Auctions online? Some Sheriff Auctions and   Government Auctions allow online bids, others are exciting live auctions in your   local area. 
What types of computer   systems can I use? All of the auctions and databases in our Members'   Area work with all computer systems, including PC's and Mac's, and all operating   systems including Microsoft Windows, Apple Macintosh, and even Linux.
If I don't have a credit   card, can I pay by check? At this time we accept credit cards   only.
If I have any other   questions, who do I contact? You may email us here.
Happy Bidding!
 

